{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ideefc1faa-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s1766b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1766b"},"text":"§ 1766b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Language training for families of officers and employees assigned abroad","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1976","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary of Agriculture is authorized to provide appropriate orientation and language training to families of officers and employees of the Department of Agriculture in anticipation of an assignment abroad of such officers and employees or while abroad pursuant to this chapter or other authority: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That the facilities of the George P. Shultz National Foreign Affairs Training Center or other Government facilities shall be used wherever practicable, and the Secretary may utilize foreign currencies generated under title I of the Food for Peace Act, as amended ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1701"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 1701","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], to carry out the purposes of this section in the foreign nations to which such officers, employees, and families are assigned. There are hereby authorized to be appropriated such sums, not to exceed $50,000 annually, as may be necessary to carry out the purposes of this section: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That for the fiscal year ending "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1977","children":[],"tail":", any appropriations available to the Secretary of Agriculture (not to exceed $50,000) may be used to carry out the purposes of this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ideefc1fab-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-28/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1954, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", title VI, § 606C, formerly § 602(f), as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/449"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–449","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1500"},"text":"90 Stat. 1500","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 606C, and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/501/tIV/s401/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–501, title IV, § 401(3)","children":[],"tail":", (4), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1691"},"text":"92 Stat. 1691","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/470/tI/s102/f"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–470, title I, § 102(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2237"},"text":"94 Stat. 2237","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/132/s1/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–132, § 1(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-01-16"},"text":"Jan. 16, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/2412"},"text":"115 Stat. 2412","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/tIII/s3001/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, title III, § 3001(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(H), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1820"},"text":"122 Stat. 1820","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ideefc1fac-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ideefc1fad-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"ideefc1fae-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Food for Peace Act, as amended, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-07-10/ch469"},"text":"act July 10, 1954, ch. 469","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/454"},"text":"68 Stat. 454","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 41 (§ 1691 et seq.) of this title. Title I of the Act is classified to subchapter II (§ 1701 et seq.) of chapter 41 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1691"},"text":"section 1691 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"ideefc1faf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/470/s102/f"},"text":"section 102(f) of Pub. L. 96–470","children":[],"tail":" was executed to this section which is section 606C of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1954","children":[],"tail":", instead of section 602(f) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1954","children":[],"tail":", as directed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/470/s102/f"},"text":"section 102(f) of Pub. L. 96–470","children":[],"tail":", as the probable intent of Congress, in view of the renumbering of section 602(f) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1954","children":[],"tail":" as section 606C of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1954","children":[],"tail":" by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/501/s401/3"},"text":"section 401(3) of Pub. L. 95–501","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions comprising this section were formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1762/f"},"text":"section 1762(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to redes­ignation by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/501/s401/3"},"text":"section 401(3) of Pub. L. 95–501","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ideefc1fb0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Food for Peace Act” for “Agricultural Trade Development and Assistance Act of 1954”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/132"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–132","children":[],"tail":" substituted “George P. Shultz National Foreign Affairs Training Center” for “Foreign Service Institute”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/470"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–470","children":[],"tail":" struck out provision requiring the Secretary of Agriculture to submit to the House Committee of Agriculture and the Senate Committee on Agriculture, Nutrition, and Forestry not later than ninety days after the end of each fiscal year a detailed report showing activities carried out u